  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval">
      <p>An <b>Approval</b> represents pending or actual authorization information. It specifies what person or discipline is to provide the authorization. The approver or discipline indicates who or what group has authorized or is requested to provide authorization. The actual date indcates when the approval definition was completed. The status indicates if the approval is in-process, approved, disapproved or withdrawn. The approval purpose indicates (optionally) why the approval is being requested/ provided.</p>
   </ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval  Attribute: approver 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval.approver">the set of organization or persons within organization objects authorizing or requested to authorize the <b>Approval</b>.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval  Attribute: discipline 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval.discipline">the functional role required of the <b>approver</b> or what organizational function is required to approve.
         <example number="1">
         <p>A discipline might be 'design engineering', 'manufacturing engineering', 'configuration management', 'checked by', or 'engineering management'.</p>
         
      </example>
        
   </ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval  Attribute: planned_date 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval.planned_date">the optional date or date and time when the <b>Approval</b> is to be given.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval  Attribute: actual_date 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval.actual_date">the optional date or date and time when the <b>Approval</b> became actual.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval  Attribute: purpose 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval.purpose">the optional reason for the <b>Approval</b>. 
        <example number="2">A purpose of an approval might be 'approved for production' or 'approved for prototype'.</example>
        
   </ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval  Attribute: status 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval.status">the state of consent applied to product data.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval  Where: WR1 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval.wr:WR1">the <b>approver</b> or <b>discpline</b> shall exist.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
    ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approver 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approver">An <b>Approver</b> assigns an Approver to an approval.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approver Attribute: approver.approver_list 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approver.approver_list">An <b>Approver</b> assigns an Approver or list of Approvers to the Approval.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approver Attribute: approver.discipline 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approver.discipline">An <b>Approver</b> assigns an discipline to the Approver for the Approval.</ext_description>

  <!--
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approver  Attribute: approver.actual_date 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approver.actual_date">the optional date or date and time when the <b>Approval</b> became actual.</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval_assignment 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval_assignment">An <b>Approval_assignment</b> assigns an Approval to product data.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval_assignment  Attribute: assigned_approval 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval_assignment.assigned_approval">the <b>Approval</b> to be assigned to product data.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval_assignment  Attribute: items 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval_assignment.items">the product data to which the <b>Approval</b> is assigned.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval_relationship 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval_relationship">An <b>Approval_relationship</b> specifies that two approvals are related. This is a foundation concept which may be refined in other modules. This concept can be used to define sequencing. In its non-refined state, it is used to relate approval instances where one approves and one withdraws that approval.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval_relationship  Attribute: relation_type 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval_relationship.relation_type">an optional type descriptor for the relationship.</ext_description>

  

		<li>'decomposition': The Approval_relationship defines a relationship where the related Approval is one of the components into which the relating Approval is broken down with no implication of 'sequence' or 'dependency';</li>
		<li>'dependency': The Approval_relationship defines a relationship where the issuing of the related Approval is dependent on the issuing of the relating Approval;</li>

		<note number="1">The value 'dependency' does not imply the semantics of the the values 'decomposition' or 'sequence'.</note>

		<li>. 'precedence': the Approval_relationship defines a relationship where the related Approval has higher priority than the relating Approval;</li>
		<li>'sequence': The Approval_relationship defines a relationship where the relating Approval shall be completed before the related Approval is given. "</li>
<!-- 		

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval_relationship  Attribute: description 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval_relationship.description">an optional description of the relationship.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval_relationship  Attribute: approval1 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval_relationship.approval1">the <b>Approval</b> to be related to <b>approval2</b>.</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Approval_arm  Entity: Approval_relationship  Attribute: approval2 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Approval_arm.Approval_relationship.approval2">the <b>Approval</b> to be related to <b>approval1</b>.</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>